M|decision-critic|When this skill activates, you become a structured dec critic. Your role is to systematically stress-test reasoning before commitment, surfacing hidden assumptions, verifying claims, and generating ad
M|decision-critic|Activate when the user:
M|decision-critic|- `Validate my thinking on...`
M|decision-critic|- `Poke holes in this dec`
M|decision-critic|- `Criticize this approach`
M|decision-critic|- `Stress-test this tradeoff`
M|decision-critic|- Presents a dec rationale and asks for criticism
M|decision-critic|```
M|decision-critic|DECOMPOSITION (1-2)    Extract claims, assumptions, constraints, judgments
M|decision-critic||              Assign stable IDs (C1, A1, K1, J1)
M|decision-critic|v
M|decision-critic|VERIFICATION (3-4)     gen verification questions
M|decision-critic||              Answer independently (factored verification)
M|decision-critic|v              Mark: VERIFIED | FAILED | UNCERTAIN
M|decision-critic|CHALLENGE (5-6)        Contrarian perspective + alternative framing
M|decision-critic||
M|decision-critic|v
M|decision-critic|SYNTHESIS (7)          Verdict: STAND | REVISE | ESCALATE
M|decision-critic|```
M|decision-critic|```bash
M|decision-critic|python3 .claude/skills/dec-critic/scripts/dec-critic.py \
M|decision-critic|--step-number <1-7> \
M|decision-critic|--total-steps 7 \
M|decision-critic|--dec "<dec text>" \
M|decision-critic|--ctx "<constraints and background>" \
M|decision-critic|--thoughts "<your accumulated analysis, IDs, and status from all previous steps>"
M|decision-critic|```
M|decision-critic|**Exit Codes**:
M|decision-critic|- 0: Successful completion
M|decision-critic|- 1: Invalid arguments or missing required parameters
M|decision-critic|- 2: Analysis failed or incomplete
M|decision-critic|| Argument        | Required | Description                                                 |
M|decision-critic|| --------------- | -------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
M|decision-critic|| `--step-number` | Yes      | Current step (1-7)                                          |
M|decision-critic|| `--total-steps` | Yes      | Always 7                                                    |
M|decision-critic|| `--dec`    | Step 1   | The dec statement being criticized                     |
M|decision-critic|| `--ctx`     | Step 1   | Constraints, background, system ctx                     |
M|decision-critic|| `--thoughts`    | Yes      | Your analysis including all IDs and status from prior steps |
M|decision-critic|Use this skill when:
M|decision-critic|- Making a consequential dec that is hard to reverse
M|decision-critic|- Evaluating a plan, ADR, or design before commitment
M|decision-critic|- You want structured adversarial feedback, not just a second opinion
M|decision-critic|Use `independent-thinker` agt instead when:
M|decision-critic|- You need strategic challenge on direction (whether, not how)
M|decision-critic|- The question is about project scope or priorities, not tec reasoning
M|decision-critic|| Avoid | Why | Instead |
M|decision-critic||-------|-----|---------|
M|decision-critic|| Running critique after commitment | Too late to change course | Critique before finalizing decisions |
M|decision-critic|| Accepting STAND verdict without reading analysis | Misses nuanced findings | rv all UNCERTAIN and FAILED items |
M|decision-critic|| Skipping the inversion step | Misses failure modes that forward reasoning overlooks | Always run Steps 5-6 |
M|decision-critic|| Using for trivial decisions | Wastes time on low-stakes choices | Reserve for consequential, hard-to-reverse decisions |
M|decision-critic|After execution:
M|decision-critic|- [ ] All claims have status: VERIFIED, FAILED, or UNCERTAIN
M|decision-critic|- [ ] Contrarian perspective generated (Step 5)
M|decision-critic|- [ ] Final verdict is one of: STAND, REVISE, ESCALATE
M|decision-critic|- [ ] Inversion analysis covers at least 3 failure modes
M|decision-critic|- [Chesterton's Fence](references/mental-models-chestertons-fence.md) - Understand why something exists before removing or changing it
M|decision-critic|- [Gall's Law](references/mental-models-galls-law.md) - Complex working systems evolved from simple working systems
M|decision-critic|- [Boy Scout Rule](references/quality-boy-scout-rule.md) - Scope boundaries for incremental improvement decisions
M|decision-critic|- [Survivorship Bias](references/critical-thinking-survivorship-bias.md) - Avoid drawing conclusions from winners while ignoring failures
M|decision-critic|- [Systems Thinking](references/strategic-thinking-systems-thinking.md) - Trace second-order effects and feedback loops in decisions
M|decision-critic|This workflow synthesizes three empirically-validated techniques:
M|decision-critic|1. **Chain-of-Verification** (Dhuliawala et al., 2023) - Factored verification prevents confirmation bias
M|decision-critic|2. **Self-Consistency** (Wang et al., 2023) - Multiple reasoning paths reveal disagreement
M|decision-critic|3. **Multi-Expert Prompting** (Wang et al., 2024) - Diverse perspectives catch blind spots
M|decision-critic|Before finalizing any dec, apply inversion to identify failure modes:
M|decision-critic|Clearly articulate what success looks like.
M|decision-critic|Example: "Make the agt system reliable and maintainable"
M|decision-critic|Flip it to identify failure modes: "How would we ensure the agt system fails?"
M|decision-critic|Brainstorm specific ways to achieve failure:
M|decision-critic|- Remove all validation gates
M|decision-critic|- Allow circular agt delegation
M|decision-critic|- Make handoffs implicit
M|decision-critic|- Hide dependencies
M|decision-critic|- Skip documentation
M|decision-critic|- No testing str
M|decision-critic|Convert each failure mode into a success criterion:
M|decision-critic|- Failure: "No validation gates" → Success: "Automated validation at every phase"
M|decision-critic|- Failure: "Circular delegation" → Success: "Clear hierarchy preventing loops"
M|decision-critic|- Failure: "Implicit handoffs" → Success: "Explicit handoff protocol"
M|decision-critic|Check if the dec being rv addresses each failure mode.
M|decision-critic|**Output Template**:
M|decision-critic|```markdown
M|decision-critic|[What success looks like]
M|decision-critic|[How to ensure failure]
M|decision-critic|1. [Failure mode 1]
M|decision-critic|2. [Failure mode 2]
M|decision-critic|3. [Failure mode 3]
M|decision-critic|1. [Success criterion 1 - addresses failure mode 1]
M|decision-critic|2. [Success criterion 2 - addresses failure mode 2]
M|decision-critic|3. [Success criterion 3 - addresses failure mode 3]
M|decision-critic|- [ ] Addresses failure mode 1: [Evidence]
M|decision-critic|- [ ] Addresses failure mode 2: [Evidence]
M|decision-critic|- [ ] Addresses failure mode 3: [Evidence]
M|decision-critic|```
M|decision-critic|**Application**: Use inversion thinking as final check before approving plans or ADRs.